nuar 1177","5 January 1161":"5. januar 1161","1189":"1189","1177":"1177","1243":"1243","1176":"1176","1161":"1161","1150":"1150","1 April 1176":"1. april 1176","about 1175":"omkring 1175","Acre, First Kingdom of Jerusalem":"Acre, Brasilien","Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland":"Toruń, kujawsko-pomorskie, Polen","Torun, , , Germany":"Thorn, Thorn, Westpreußen, Preußen, Tyskland"},"nl":{"5 January 1161–10 Jan 1177":"5 januari 1161–10 januari 1177","1150–1189":"1150–1189","1176–1243":"1176–1243","1161–1177":"1161–1177","10 Jan 1177":"10 januari 1177","5 January 1161":"5 januari 1161","1189":"1189","1177":"1177","1243":"1243","1176":"1176","1161":"1161","1150":"1150","1 April 1176":"1 april 1176","about 1175":"circa 1175","Acre, First Kingdom of Jerusalem":"Acre, Brazilië","Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland":"Toruń, kujawsko-pomorskie, Polen","Torun, , , Germany":"Thorn, Thorn, Westpreußen, Preußen, Duitsland"},"en":{"5 January 1161–10 Jan 1177":"5 January 1161–10 January 1177","1150–1189":"1150–1189","1176–1243":"1176–1243","1161–1177":"1161–1177","10 Jan 1177":"10 January 1177","5 January 1161":"5 January 1161","1189":"1189","1177":"1177","1243":"1243","1176":"1176","1161":"1161","1150":"1150","1 April 1176":"1 April 1176","about 1175":"about 1175","Acre, First Kingdom of Jerusalem":"Acre, Brazil","Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland":"Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland","Torun, , , Germany":"Thorn, Thorn, West Prussia, Prussia, Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"of","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese: Cheng, Jing, Kam Fung, Wai Shing, Wing, Yali, Yuk.","Chinese:","variant Romanization of the surnames 歐 and 區, see   Ou   1 and 2."],"variants":[{"name":"Ou","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Wei, Ying, Ching, Heng, Hong, Jia, Kuang Yu, Li-Ching, Cho, Chong, Chung, Sa.  Southeast Asian Lichun, Ming, Quan, Roeun, Sokhom, Chau, Hai, Leang, Ly, Nhanh, Phan, Pho, Tha.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 歐, meaning ‘to sing someone's praise’ in ancient Chinese: (i) from the placename Dong Ou (東甌), a fief (in present-day Wenzhou in Zhejiang province) which was granted to Yao in 192  BC . It is said that Yao was a descendant of Wujiang (reigned 355–333  BC ), king of the state of Yue (located mainly in present-day Zhejiang and Jiangxi provinces) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (ii) from the placename Ou Yu (歐餘), the name of a fief (located in present-day Zhejiang province) that was granted to Ti, the second son of Wujiang (reigned 355–333  BC ), king of the state of Yue (located mainly in present-day Zhejiang and Jiangxi provinces) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 區, originally denoting an ancient vessel for measurement in ancient Chinese: from the personal name of <i>Ou Zhizi</i> (歐治子), an expert sword-maker who lived during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). Some of his descendants inherited <i>Ou</i> (歐) as their surname, simplifying the Chinese character 歐 to 區."]}]},{"name":"Acre","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Acker   2 (or   Ackers   without the excrescent <i>-s</i>).","In some cases also an Americanized form of Norwegian   Aakre  , German or Dutch   Acker   or   Aker   (see also   Achor  ), and possibly also of some other similar (like-sounding) Scandinavian or German surname."],"variants":[{"name":"Acker","meanings":["Dutch and German: topographic name from Middle High German and Middle Dutch <i>acker</i> ‘(cultivated) field’ (a cognate of the English word <i>acre</i>), hence a byname for a peasant (see   Ackerman  ). Compare   Achor  ,   Acre  ,   Acree  , and   Auker  .","English: habitational name from Castle Acre, South Acre, or West Acre in Norfolk; or a topographic name for someone living by a piece of cultivated land, from Middle English <i>aker</i>, <i>acre</i> ‘acre, field’ (Old English <i>æcer</i>). Compare   Akers  .","Jewish (Ashkenazic): artificial name from German <i>Acker</i> ‘field’ (see 1 above)."]}]},{"name":"Marita","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["diminutive form of   Sara  , now also sometimes used as an independent first name in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Marita of Acre was born on 5 January 1161, in Acre, Brazil. She married Sir Otto of Acre about 1175, in Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 10 January 1177, in Thorn, Thorn, West Prussia, Prussia, Germany, at the age of 16."},"et":{"5 January 1161–10 Jan 1177":"5. jaanuar 1161–10. jaanuar 1177","1150–1189":"1150–1189","1176–1243":"1176–1243","1161–1177":"1161–1177","10 Jan 1177":"10. jaanuar 1177","5 January 1161":"5. jaanuar 1161","1189":"1189","1177":"1177","1243":"1243","1176":"1176","1161":"1161","1150":"1150","1 April 1176":"1. aprill 1176","about 1175":"umbes 1175","Acre, First Kingdom of Jerusalem":"Acre, Brasiilia","Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland":"Toruń, kujawsko-pomorskie, Poola","Torun, , , Germany":"Thorn, Thorn, Westpreußen, Preußen, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"5 January 1161–10 Jan 1177":"5. tammikuuta 1161–10. tammikuuta 1177","1150–1189":"1150–1189","1176–1243":"1176–1243","1161–1177":"1161–1177","10 Jan 1177":"10. tammikuuta 1177","5 January 1161":"5. tammikuuta 1161","1189":"1189","1177":"1177","1243":"1243","1176":"1176","1161":"1161","1150":"1150","1 April 1176":"1. huhtikuuta 1176","about 1175":"noin 1175","Acre, First Kingdom of Jerusalem":"Acre, Brasilia","Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland":"Toruń, kujawsko-pomorskie, Puola","Torun, , , Germany":"Thorn, Thorn, Westpreußen, Preußen, Saksa"},"fr":{"5 January 1161–10 Jan 1177":"5 janvier 1161–10 janvier 1177","1150–1189":"1150–1189","1176–1243":"1176–1243","1161–1177":"1161–1177"